General.Name: Aasen Sparebank
General.Description: Aasen Sparebank provides various banking products and services in Norway. The company accepts various deposits and accounts, as well as bank cards; and offers payment, payment terminals, billing, credit, overdraft, leasing, bank guarantee, pension, and online and mobile banking services. It also provides construction, business, car, mortgage, and small loans, as well as loans for other vehicles; and small loans refinancing services. In addition, the company offers employee and business liability, health, personal, occupational injury, travel, collective accident, store, data attack, property damage, office, homeowners, craftsman, and business insurance products; and farmer's accident, farm building agriculture, farmer's car, poultry, horse, pet, home agriculture, operating equipment and crops, and agricultural machinery insurance products, as well as insurance for goods during transport, ATV, work machines, taxis, commercial vehicles, and trailers. Aasen Sparebank was founded in 1862 and is based in Åsen, Norway.
